2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: The historic Sonic the Hedgehog and Mega Man crossover event rolls on! The hunt for the Roboticized Masters continues as Sonic and Mega Man face down Shadow Man and - Shadow Man? Meanwhile, Drs. Eggman and Wily gloat over the captive Dr. Light. But what is the brilliant, bearded scientist preparing to do? Featuring stunning new cover art from Patrick 'SPAZ' Spaziante, and a special throwback variant cover you just can't miss!

MASTER AGAINST MASTER

Just as the S-class wizard test gets underway, everything goes wrong! Grimoire Heart launches a surprise attack on Fairy Tail. But the guild is just collateral damage – their real goal is much more sinister. At the vanguard of the invasion force is Grimoire Heart’s master, Hades… a man who only respects power, and has a history with Makarov!

ULTIMATES DISASSEMBLED PART TWO!!!

A new dark force has taken the reigns of the world

The Ultimates are no more. Long live the XXREDACTEDXX

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: Drawn to danger, Dejah Thoris has survived murder plots and bloody global conflicts. After these recent events, the royal family insists that she take a quiet, safe holiday. But her sojourn of relaxation turns into a nightmare, as the young princess bears witness to a dangerous discovery in an unknown region of Barsoom!
"UNDERCLOUD" ends here! With the Metal Men in tow, can Batman thwart Rebel One's plan to level Neo-Gotham?
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Undercloud, Part Six: Extended Family

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: In the Fortress of Solitude, the Kents confront Luthor over his plans to give other people super powers. Meanwhile, Superman confronts the Flash over...a game of chess?
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Chapter 26

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: John Carter might be the brand-new Warlord of Mars, but his his honeymoon's gonna be real short. The savage green Martians start running amok the moment he ascends the throne, threatening to smash the fragile peace he has fought so hard to win. What's behind the uptick in violence? Only John Carter and his old pal Tars Tarkas can find the truth. Warlord of Mars #26 is the first installment of the thrilling Savages of Mars story arc. John Carter's exploits on the Red Planet are just beginning!
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: The Green Menace: Savages of Mars Part 1 of 6

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description:
Meet the Juice Squeezers: a group of elementary-school kids tasked with secretly keeping their small town safe from a horrible, underground epidemic—written and drawn by David Lapham! Learn about a vampire couple during the time of the Black Plague in Steve Niles and menton3’s The Nosferatu Wars! Join bounty hunter Mercy St. Clair on a vacation gone horribly wrong in Ron Randall’s Trekker!

Plus, new installments of Buffy, Blackout, Nexus, Crime Does Not Pay, Underground, Alabaster: Boxcar Tales, and Bloodhound!

David Lapham writes and draws a gory all-ages story.

The original reunited team of Excel, Hyatt and Elgala stand before the throne of their lord—only for Excel to perform a blasphemous gesture of disloyalty, and for Il Palazzo to issue the most shocking order Excel could ever imagine! As Shiouji comes to realize the truth about both his father and his mother, Matsuya is ready to make a decision that will open the forbidden door at last. Warning: you have been misled!
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Vol. 26

"SPIDER-MAN NO MORE" CONTINUES

SPIDER-MAN is back!!

Will CLOAK, DAGGER, BOMBSHELL, SPIDER-WOMAN and SPIDEY be enough to take down the evil ROXXON CORPORATION?

And what is Miles' new girlfriend's secret?

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Flowers for Bizarro, Part 2 of 3

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: The conflict between the Klingon and Romulan Empires erupts, with Captain Kirk and the crew of the Enterprise trapped in the middle! Don't miss the newest chapter of the ongoing series overseen by Star Trek Into Darkness writer/producer Roberto Orci!
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: The Khitomer Conflict, Part 2 of 4

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: This issue is filled with sick humor! Because SpongeBob has a bad cold. And when his friends visit, things somehow get worse. Joey Weiser and Gregg Schigiel reveal all in 'Sick Day.' And in 'Trench Vanilla,' readers can experience a SpongeBob adventure in widescreen - that's right, it's a 10-page comic that is one continuous image! Enjoy this miracle of comic book technology courtesy of Robert Leighton and Gregg Schigiel. Plus: James Kochalka's 'SpongeFunnies,' David Lewman and Vanessa Davis' 'Squidward in Love,' Joey Weiser's 'Phoney Dance Party,' and Maris Wicks' 'Flotsam and Jetsam.'

From Barsoom to the cold winds of Cimmeria, Draw!, the professional 'how-to' magazine on comics and animation, interviews legendary illustrator Joe Jusko as he explains and illustrates his process creating some of the top fantasy art being produced today! Plus, Jamar Nicholas interviews Jimm Rugg, the artist behind Street Angel and The Guild. Draw! also welcomes new regular contributor Jerry Ordway with the debut of a regular feature on his behind-the-scenes working process as an industry legend.
Batman works to contain a swarm of genetically altered killer bats, as well as She-Bat and other humans who have been mutated into bat-people.
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Crown of Fear

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: Luke’s journey to Italy gets him deeper into the criminal underworld – unfortunately for him, that means fighting superpowered villains in a death tournament where he can’t use the Batwing armor!
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: When in Rome (Sort of)

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: All hell breaks loose as Superman is caught between an alien menace and the super-powered soldier the U.S. Army has sent to kill it!
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Monster

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: “THE OUTSIDERS WAR” begins here! Oliver Queen finally knows the location of the Outsiders’ base, but first he must return to the place where Green Arrow was born: The Island! Secrets are revealed, new villains introduced, and a mind-blowing final page kicks off this new storyline with a bang!
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: The Outsiders War, Book 1: Return to the Island

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: Still in disarray after the events of “LIGHTS OUT,” Hal and Kilowog struggle to enforce the Corps’ new directive against Star Sapphire Nol-Anj! Having revealed a command of the Violet light unlike any the Corps has encountered before, Hal makes an earth-shaking decision. Is his win-at-all-costs attitude exactly the kind of leadership the Corps needs, or is he walking them into their next trap?
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Superior Force

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: The Avatar of the Green has something to prove, and he’s going to do it by killing Animal Man and/or destroying the world—not necessarily in that order! Plus, the origin of Swamp Thing’s newest foe, the implacable Seeder, in a story filled with cameos from some of the DCU’s darkest magical denizens!
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Victor: Spoiled

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: Storm Control decides to trade one peril to Earth for another while Stormwatch teams up with a mega-powered cosmic dynamo, and we finally get to meet Extremax the Omega in the flesh!
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Legacy

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: He's fought everything from giant robots to bionic bigfoot and lived to tell about it. But when Steve's best friend becomes his mortal enemy it will be the fight of his life. When the smoke clears, the Bionic Man and OSI will be changed forever.

Daredevil battles Psylocke! The Avengers challenge the power of the X-Men! The long-lost secrets of the Iron Fist are revealed!

By Brian Michael Bendis, Mike Dedoato, Rick Remender and Brandon Peterson!

Includes material reprinted from: Avengers vs X-Men #6, AVX #6, New Avengers #26 and 29.

ZERO YEAR continues! With Gotham City thrown into total chaos by The Riddler, Batman and Jim Gordon must learn to work together! This issue is also offered as a combo pack edition with a redemption code for a digital download of this issue.
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Zero Year: Dark City, Part Three

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: With the events of FOREVER EVIL looming, Nightwing enters the final stages of life as he knows it!
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Some Strings Attached

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: The shocking conclusion of “Batgirl: Wanted”! Can Barbara save her father’s life without compromising the truth about her brother’s death?
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Ambush

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description:
A FOREVER EVIL tie-in! With a murderous King Shark on her tail, Amanda Waller must go deeper into the depths of Belle Reve to free a mysterious prisoner so dangerous that only she knows of his existence! Meanwhile, it’s a battle royale between the Squad’s two Gotham City psychos: Harley Quinn and James Gordon, Jr.!

For reasons still unclear, Killer Shark and his father, Kamo, are fighting to kill each other. Meanwhile, Amanda Waller tries to come up with a way to have the two powerhouses turn their rage towards the OMAC and The Thinker.

James Gordon Jr, fights Harley Quinn and tricks her into a Suicide Collar.

The Thinker gets a hold of the OMAC and attacks Kamo, giving Waller the opportunity she needs to escape.

Deadshot is still alive, and declares he is going to kill Quinn for dropping a mountain on him.

Throughout this whole issue, Waller retells the story of how she found Kamo, raised Killer Shark and the first time she witnessed the true power of OMAC.
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Aloha!

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description:
It’s Lantern vs. Lantern as John Stewart battles Hal Jordan for the leadership of the Corps! For months, John Stewart has let his anger build as Hal Jordan sent Guy Gardner into the Red Lanterns and declared war against other corps across the spectrum. After the devastating events of “LIGHTS OUT,” John is determined to rebuild the Corps as he sees fit—even if it means taking down his oldest friend!

Notes:

  • The cover is a homage to the cover of Green Lantern #3.
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Homecoming

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: Lost in time with the Teen Titans, Superboy comes to some startling revelations about his origins and future! Can he and the team rescue Kid Flash and find the way back to their own era?
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: To Hell and Back

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: It’s double trouble as Batman investigates Harvey Dent’s past to try to find him in the present—but is he ready to face the dark truth behind Two-Face’s origin?
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: The Big Burn: Ignition

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: The last stand of Jason Todd? Ra’s al Ghul is back and more powerful than ever! The Outlaws are being held captive and Jason Todd has lost his memories…can things get any worse for the team?
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Remembering

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description:
Animal Man in outer space! How did this happen? And what will Buddy find on “THE SEED PLANET”?

Buddy Baker finds himself on a new planet surrounded by angry aliens who attack him. Animal Man is lost not being able to tap into any animal powers nearby, but when he taps into the power of the largest alien, he is able to defeat it and survive. He is then approached by Bridgewalker, who tells him he is on Seed Planet and he has been chosen to be Seed Planet's new protector.

Animal Man, refuses at first but then makes a deal, Bridgewalker will send him back to the Red and then when his family is safe he will become Seed Planet's protector for the rest of his life.

Brigewalker, after giving Animal Man new power, sends Buddy back to the Red where he becomes face to face with the King of the Limbs, who plans on killing Buddy, just like Brother Blood will kill Maxine.
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Godseed

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: The planet of Exuro is a paradise—but at a terrible cost: They’re literally stealing from their own futures! When the Exurans cross the line and bring the wrath of the cosmos down on themselves, it’s up to Kyle Rayner to resolve the conflict…but what exactly do the New Guardians want him to see about the difficult choice he’ll have to make?
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Yesterday's Gone

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: Wonder Woman’s brother and sister are being held hostage by none other than Cassandra, the sadistic sibling she hasn’t even met yet! And speaking of hostages, we’re taking bets on how long chains can hold the First Born!
2013-06-01|2014-12-30.name: Nowhereland

2013-06-01|2014-12-30.description: The Birds strike back! Canary cuts loose against Regulus! Condor cuts loose on Tsiklon! Batgirl and Strix cut loose on everybody! Will it be enough for them to escape with their lives?

But a striking new foe prepares to welcome Supergirl home: LOBO! What could the mysterious new character want from Supergirl? Find out as the hot new creative team of writer Tony Bedard (GREEN LANTERN: NEW GUARDIANS) and artist Yildiray Cinar (EARTH 2) launch Supergirl into the next stage of her life in the DC Universe!

A FOREVER EVIL tie-in! Why has the Crime Syndicate really come to our Earth? What are their darkest secrets? And how will their actions fundamentally change the Justice League as we know it? Meanwhile, Grid controls the world’s power and communications, but what does he truly want from the Syndicate? Plus, a member of the League struggling to survive plots a path of return...and revenge.

The limitless power of the Elder Gods lives within a child who has fallen under the shroud of the Devourer of Souls. The fate of creation falls to the warrior Conan, who must travel to the underworld and make a pact with an old adversary—the malefic sorcerer Thulsa Doom! The epic conclusion is here! As all roads have led back to Fabletown, Cinderella leads the battle against the seemingly endless onslaught of mice/mundy hybrids! This one has it all: Blood! Guts! Romance! Swordplay! Magic! Mystery! Noble sacrifice! And...cheese? Read it before the clock strikes midnight!

ARMOR HUNTERS unleashes an all-new starting point for the world’s most wanted hero – X-O Manowar – right here with a brand new story arc by Robert Venditti (Green Lantern, The Flash) and Diego Bernard (Eternal Warrior)!

Abducted from his own time by a vicious alien race, the courageous Visigoth warrior known as Aric of Dacia spent years in slavery among the stars before escaping with his captors’ most feared weapon – the X-O Manowar armor. Now, stranded in the modern day, the world’s most primitive man also just happens to wield its most powerful weapon. But what is the X-O Manowar armor? And who before Aric of Dacia dared to wield its incalculable power? The ARMOR HUNTERS hold the key to the armor’s untold history and – one way or another – they’ll crush anything that dares threaten their secret.

Quella che fu la gloriosa capitale dell’impero romano d’Oriente non è che una città sotto assedio, ormai prossima a capitolare di fronte alla forza incontenibile degli Ottomani. Prima che il suo destino si compia, l’imperatore decide però di affidare ai fedeli guerrieri variaghi della sua guardia personale una missione vitale: insieme a un giovane capitano di ventura veneziano, dovranno affrontare un pericoloso viaggio per mettere al sicuro un tesoro tanto prezioso quanto misterioso…
